KW  - Monetary policy
KW  - Liquidity effects
KW  - Job creation and job destruction
AB  - This paper integrates the modern theory of unemployment with a limited participation model of money and asks whether such a framework can produce correlations like those associated with the Phillips curve as well as realistic labor market dynamics. The model incorporates both monetary and real shocks. The response of the economy to monetary policy shocks is consistent with recent evidence about the impact of these shocks on the economy.
